      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"5. ROUND OF BUCKS has been mixing form lately, hitting the frame two back before finishing seventh (17.58) at this track in a Class 3. Better than latest and can atone here. 7. GOTCHA TANE has not raced since scoring (18.10) over 295m at this track four-and-a-half months ago. Did finish third in a four dog trial (17.16) on this track over 295m. Overall strike-rate good and can feature with the right run. 6. MITCHAM ERIC could not have been more impressive last start in his an excellent 17.10 win at this track over 295m. Bold showing expected again. 4. OFFICER RIDLEY jumped best and was never headed last time. Will be thereabouts despite rising in class.\",\"runners\":[5,7,6,4],\"exclusive\":false}",
